article.headline: Loyola of Chicago 68, Albany, N.Y. 56
article.story: CHICAGO -- Ben Averkamp scored 17 points and Geoff McCammon added 16 to lead Loyola Chicago to a 68-56 victory against Albany on Tuesday night. Terrance Hill added 13 points for Loyola (9-2), which won its fifth straight. Averkamp had nine rebounds. Fran Urli led Albany (4-9) with 12 points. The Ramblers never trailed, scoring the first seven points and maintaining a double-digit cushion for much of the game.
